- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and sentence classification.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper compares different neural network models for sentence classification.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for natural language processing.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper focuses on neural network models.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category, but still possible as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks and the paper compares their performance on sentence classification.
